<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 16 at 3:31PM EDT  by NWS Raleigh</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northern Person
County through 430 PM EDT...
At 330 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Semora, or near Turbeville, moving northeast at 15 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Roxboro, Concord, Bethel Hill, Hyco Lake, Mayo Reservoir and Hyco
Marina.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.
Heavy rain from this storm could produce localized flooding and
ponding.</instruction>
